&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Deputy Clinical Nurse Manager&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting development opportunity has arisen for a nurse to work on Ruby Lodge which is part of the Becton Centre for Children and young people.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ruby Lodge is an in-patient provision for 8-17 year olds with learning disabilities and mental health difficulties.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The post holder will work alongside the nurse manager and two other deputies providing management support to the nursing establishment and clinical shifts on the ward.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are committed to developing this role and offer supportive and effective clinical and line management supervision alongside many other development opportunities within SCHFT.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For information and discussion regarding this role please contact Nicky Windle (Matron In- Patient CAMHS) on Sheffield 0114 3053104&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
